Path: godot/tutorials/editor/game_embedding.rst
Summary: Explains the "Select mode" option in the Godot editor and how it affects node selection.

Select mode
This option is only effective when the interaction mode is set to 2D or 3D, not Input.

When enabling "Select mode", the default behavior of showing a list of selectable nodes at the clicked position is disabled. However, this functionality can still be accessed while in select mode by pressing Ctrl + Alt + Right mouse button at the desired location.
---CHUNK---
