Summary: This section describes a feature that displays a list of selectable nodes at the clicked position, useful for selecting overlapping nodes in 2D or 3D interaction modes.

This shows a list of selectable nodes at the position clicked. This is useful when multiple nodes are overlapping and you want to select a specific one. This feature is only effective if the interaction mode is 2D or 3D, not Input. When enabling this option, select mode is disabled.
---CHUNK---
Document: Game Embedding Tutorial
Path: godot/tutorials/editor/game_embedding.rst
Summary: This section describes how to toggle the visibility of node selection highlights in the game view.
When the interaction mode is 2D or 3D, node selections are normally highlighted with an orange rectangle or box. This option allows you to toggle the visibility of these highlights. When enabled, the selection appears as a closed eye icon. If this option is enabled, future selections will not be highlighted in the game view, but they will still be selected for inspection in the Inspector dock. This is useful for reducing visual clutter in the game view.
---CHUNK---
